The paper proposes a technique for improving the performance of deep neural networks on image classification tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of binary linear classifiers, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for energy-efficient detection of natural errors, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses various image classification datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
